programmes.show_description: No Safety In Numbers. Two pairs of survivalists must take on the deadly jungles of Panama side-by-side. But before their 21-day challenge begins, they have a big decision to make. S5, Ep14

Lerner House. The crew travels to Orange, Virginia, to salvage archways, columns and windows from a 1930s brick mansion. Then, Mike and Tay build a coffee table from a door. S8, Ep13
Downtown Kannapolis. Mike and Tay have a consultation for a project from a brewery. But before they can start building they have a salvage job in Kannapolis, North Carolina. S9, Ep1
No Country For Cold Men. Vernon runs out of patience when one of his divers struggles with the freezing temperatures. Plus, Zeke is left frustrated by unexpected flooding. S10, Ep23
Dive Till You Drop. Vernon tries to capitalise on clear weather by sending out two talented divers. Zeke attempts a marathon dive, while Kris has another nightmare day. S10, Ep24
Jacqui and Andrew blaze a new trail into a remote corner of Fish Creek doesn't go according to plan. McGhie's hunch on a new dig site pulls in big gold. S9, Ep5
Toxic Invader. Fisherman and adventurer, Jeremy Wade, travels to western Australia to discover what is wiping out many of the fish in Australia's Fitzroy River. What will he find? S1, Ep6
Everything on the Line. It's a bad start to the crab season as skippers Keith and Phil await medical test results, while repairs to the rest of the boats mean they're all in debt. S5, Ep1
Red Skies in the Morning. A severe storm whips up massive 20ft waves, so most of the boats head for home. But one boat sends out a mayday. Can the coastguard reach it in time? S5, Ep2
Treasure And Tragedy. After finding evidence of a 1700s-era lifeboat near shore, Darrell and the team discover the shipwreck it came from. But a sudden tragedy hits the expedition. S2, Ep4
Out Of Thin Air. Josh's quest takes him from the frozen slopes of Mount Everest to the isolated forests of Bhutan. He uses bait to try and force an encounter with the beast. S1, Ep3
Unmasking The Myth. In the finale, Josh rafts into the remotest corners of Bhutan to capture some of his best evidence yet of the reclusive Yeti. S1, Ep4
Trust Or Die. The Deeters are dog-mushers from Alaska, with a distrust of outsiders. But when disaster strikes, the Raneys must convince them to make drastic changes to their home. S1, Ep3
Under Siege. Josh and Kim raise pigs in Virginia. But with pigs destroying their homestead and predators killing livestock, is it time to let go of their free-range dream? S1, Ep4
Rookies Are The Bomb. Desperate to move more rock, the rookies get a lesson in the dangerous art of bomb-making. Plus, Kelly is forced to sell her precious reserve of stones. S1, Ep6
Cave-Ins And Explosions. With the end of the season approaching, the rookies risk cave-ins at their abandoned mine claim. Deep underground, George is trapped in the blast zone. S1, Ep7
Lunatic Fringe. While Johnathan struggles with a rogue deckhand, skipper Jake prepares for the birth of his baby. Plus, a hydraulic explosion calls Zack's dedication into question. S11, Ep10
New Captain on the Block. While Jake Anderson prepares to captain the Saga for the first time, Captain Andy Hillstrand returns to find the Time Bandit in disarray. S11, Ep11
In St Davids, the crew help an injured fisherman onboard a Belgian trawler. In Dun Laoghaire, a paddleboarder drifts out to sea in an offshore wind. S6, Ep9
In Portrush, the crew rescue a boy in trouble after jumping off rocks. In Eastbourne, the crew help a woman who has drifted out to sea on her paddleboard. S6, Ep10
The Dust Devils' critical water supply runs dry. Jacqui and Andrew find their biggest nugget so far, while the Poseidon Crew are hit by torrential rain. S6, Ep10
Stomping Grounds. Elite survivalists Matt and Gary are tested by deadly spitting cobras and territorial elephants in an African killing zone, whilst also protecting a novice. S5, Ep15

Laverock Hill Estate. The crew heads to Glenside, Pennsylvania, to salvage a huge estate. They try to save columns, doors, mantles, bathtubs and more from the sprawling mansion. S9, Ep2
Price Fuller Machine Shop. The team heads over to the machine shop they bought, to see what they can find before renovating the house and determining how many new builds are needed. S9, Ep3
Blood In The Water Part 2. Jake must confront his disorderly crew, forcing him to make a tough decision. Meanwhile, Keith deals with a knife injury to one of his deckhands. S15, Ep4
Winter Is Here. The coldest weather in nearly a decade threatens to crush hulls and freeze the sea. Meanwhile, a shocking mishap leaves one of the Hansens grasping for their life. S15, Ep8
Tough Inheritance. With winter intensifying, Sean faces an engine room fire. Plus, Harley offers his nephew a job as a deckhand, but the rest of the crew are not impressed. S15, Ep9
Baptism By Fire. The Cheals take on their most dangerous dig ever. The Bushmen trial a rookie to operate their exploration drill, but it doesn't go as smoothly as they'd hoped. S6, Ep2
In Search Of Fuel. The Opal Whisperers work underground together for the first time on a legendary claim. The Mooka Boys are forced to work Leif's late father's abandoned mine. S6, Ep3
A Well That Takes On Water. The Digi Diggers need to explore new ground after mining opal too brittle to sell. The Bushmen find their new claim has been dug out by opal thieves. S6, Ep4
Diggers, Dingoes & Debt. Patrick and Kirsty search for rare Aquamarine crystals on their remote Queensland lease. Plus, Frankie & Ebriony face off against wild pigs and dingoes. S1, Ep3
Hour Of Need. Hugh and Jarrin need a miracle to keep their mining operation alive. Plus, Patrick and Kirsty are desperate for an $80,000 payday of high-grade crystals. S1, Ep4
Mookaite N Miracles. The Rockhounds need a miracle to turn their season around. Kirsty and Patrick need to find rare Ocean Kyanite crystals to have a chance of recouping their debt. S1, Ep5
Permit delays force the Poseidon Crew off road as they try to survive the season. Plus, the Dust Devils gamble big in the hope of finding fine gold. S5, Ep7
Marcus and Linden fear a flat battery could leave them stuck in the outback for days. Plus, Shane and Russell attempt to get their season on track. S5, Ep8
A wet plant disaster threatens the Dust Devils' potentially lucrative fine gold find. Plus, the Gold Timers desperately try to turn their season around. S5, Ep9
I Can't Breathe. Larina is on the verge of losing custody of her child due to her hoarding. But when confronted to let go of her clutter, her compulsion threatens to win the battle. S3, Ep9
I'm Dumbfounded. After years of hoarding, Vickie and Jeff's marriage is at its breaking point. Now, Vickie reveals the secrets she's been keeping. Will they save their marriage? S3, Ep13
Nantucket Mermaid. A mermaid serenades a commercial fisherman. Plus, a shadow figure scuffles with a small dog, and a ghost blows out birthday candles. S7, Ep7
Mountain Oaks Mayhem. The crew investigate rumours of dark forces at an abandoned home in La Crescenta, California. Did Charles Manson put a curse on the family who lived there? S20, Ep13
Petrified In Pahrump. The crew are in Nevada to investigate a winery that's been plagued by fatal accidents. The terrified staff claim they are being stalked by an evil presence. S20, Ep14
